#: class-my-apps.php:758
msgid "Abilities for searching the My Apps App Store, reading What can I do? guides, and customizing the My Apps launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:774
msgid "Get All My Apps State"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:775
msgid "Returns the full My Apps launcher state, including background, visible app order, and app metadata."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:782
msgid "Use this before answering questions about the user's My Apps launcher, launcher apps, visible app order, hidden apps, app icons, app links, or background. The result is the full current launcher state; use visible_ordered for display order and each app's hidden field for visibility."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:795
msgid "Get What Can I Do Guides"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:796
msgid "Returns the default My Apps What can I do? guide catalog for answering what users can do with WordPress."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:803
msgid "Optional guide slug to return one guide."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:807
msgid "Optional search query matched against guide titles, descriptions, and steps."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:811
msgid "Optional maximum number of matching guides to return."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:822
msgid "Use this when the user asks what they can do with WordPress, asks for activity ideas, or asks for What can I do? guide steps. This returns only the default recipes.json catalog; it does not include browser-local custom blueprints or alternate App Store catalog sources."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:835
msgid "Search My Apps App Store"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:836
msgid "Searches or browses the built-in My Apps App Store catalog of installable apps and curated plugin recommendations."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:843
msgid "Optional search query matched against app titles, descriptions, authors, categories, paths, plugin slugs, and GitHub repositories."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:847
msgid "Optional App Store category to return, such as Apps, AI, Media, Productivity, Social, Utility, Custom, or Other Plugins."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:852
msgid "Optional entry type filter. Use app for blueprint apps, plugin for curated plugin recommendations, or all."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:856
msgid "Whether to include curated plugin recommendations. Defaults to the current My Apps simplified WordPress mode setting."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:860
msgid "Optional maximum number of matching App Store entries to return."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:871
msgid "Use this when the user asks whether My Apps has an app store, asks to search or browse the app store, asks what apps can be installed from My Apps, or asks about curated app/plugin recommendations. This reads the default published catalog and cannot include browser-local custom blueprints or alternate catalog source overrides."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:884
msgid "Set My Apps Background"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:885
msgid "Updates the My Apps launcher background preference."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:893
msgid "A preset background slug, image attachment ID, remote image URL, or safe CSS color/gradient background."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:903
msgid "Use this when the user asks to change the My Apps launcher background. Pass one accepted background slug, an image attachment ID, a remote image URL, or a safe CSS color/gradient background."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:916
msgid "Add My Apps Icon"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:917
msgid "Adds a custom app icon to the My Apps launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:926
msgid "The app icon label shown in the launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:930
#: class-my-apps.php:972
msgid "The URL opened by the app icon."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:933
msgid "Optional icon. Omit all icon fields to use a generated letter icon."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:942
msgid "Use this when the user asks to add or pin an app icon to the My Apps launcher. Provide a name and URL. Provide at most one icon value: icon_url, dashicon, emoji, gradient, icon { type, value }, or use_favicon."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:955
msgid "Set My Apps App Details"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:956
msgid "Renames an app or changes its link in the My Apps launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:964
#: class-my-apps.php:1009
#: class-my-apps.php:1047
msgid "The launcher app slug from my-apps/get-all."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:968
msgid "The app label shown in the launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:976
msgid "When true, remove the custom name and URL override."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:986
msgid "Use this when the user asks to rename an app, change an app shortcut link, or revert a custom app name/link. First call my-apps/get-all to find the slug. Provide name and/or url, or set revert to true."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:999
msgid "Set My Apps App Icon"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1000
msgid "Updates the icon graphic for an existing My Apps launcher app."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1013
msgid "When true, remove the custom icon override and return to the app-provided icon."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1016
msgid "New icon value. Use icon type letter to force a generated letter icon."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1025
msgid "Use this when the user asks to change the icon for an existing My Apps launcher app. First call my-apps/get-all to find the slug. Provide exactly one icon value unless reverting."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1038
msgid "Set My Apps App Visibility"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1039
msgid "Shows or hides an app in the My Apps launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1051
msgid "Whether the app should be hidden from the launcher."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1061
msgid "Use this when the user asks to hide, show, restore, or unhide one app in the My Apps launcher. First call my-apps/get-all to find the slug. Set hidden to true to hide the app, or false to restore it. For multiple visibility or order changes, prefer my-apps/set-visible-ordered."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1074
msgid "Set My Apps Visible Ordered Apps"
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1075
msgid "Sets the visible My Apps launcher icons and their order."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1083
msgid "Launcher app slugs that should be visible, in display order. Apps not listed are hidden."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1096
msgid "Use this when the user asks to reorder visible apps, hide multiple apps, or show only specific apps. First call my-apps/get-all to find app slugs and the current visible_ordered array. Pass visible_ordered as the complete desired visible slug list in display order; every app omitted from visible_ordered is hidden. Verify the response using visible_ordered and each app's hidden field."
msgstr ""

